{"type":"message","id":"2f1feb0e","parentId":"118f9ae0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:44:42.600Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_909pw7ojyv4j_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 044413\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine my next action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals document:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- Key pending task: \"Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\" as the next action for the TIC Experiment\r\n- The current pulse log is `pulse_2026-03-24 044316.md`\r\n\r\nMy next concrete action should be to implement the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier as outlined in the pending Phase 1 Advancement section.\r\n\r\nLet me check what logs exist and implement the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the immediate next step per Phase 1 Advancement. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant structure across pulse logs to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script that will analyze pulse logs to identify invariants and measure classification accuracy. This is the concrete experiment implementation needed to validate the key hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\nTest hypothesis: **Causal structure IS invariant structure**\r\n- Invariant = patterns that persist across sessions (causal)\r\n- Variant = patterns that change/decode (ephemeral)\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Input\r\n- Pulse logs from `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- Target: last 20 pulse logs\r\n\r\n### Classification Task\r\nFor each unit in a pulse:\r\n1. **Temporal Invariance Test**: Does this pattern appear in ≥K prior sessions?\r\n2. **Cross-Session Stability**: Does it appear in ≥70% of subsequent sessions?\r\n\r\n### Invariant Criteria (λ-tuned)\r\n- Appears in K+ prior sessions\r\n- Stability ratio ≥ threshold\r\n- Decay rate ≤ λ\r\n\r\n### Variant Criteria\r\n- Appears in <K sessions\r\n- Stability ratio < threshold\r\n- Decay rate > λ\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- [ ] >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy from invariants\r\n\r\n## Implementation Phases\r\n1. Parse pulse logs, extract content units\r\n2. Build temporal occurrence matrix\r\n3. Apply λ-threshold classifier\r\n4. Validate against held-out sessions\r\n5. Measure prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Generated: 2026-03-24 | Status: READY FOR IMPLEMENTATION*\r\nfile: experiments/TIC/experiment_design.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:44:28\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774341882598}}
